160th Street, east side, just north of Jamaica Avenue, showing the
Queensborough Real Estate (2.B.R.E.) Exchange.
P. L. Sperr  March 25, 1932

Jamaica Avenue, north side, east from 160th to 162nd Streets. The corner house is Crawford's liquor and wine place, specialising in Jos. Sallert beer and Schmidt's Kloster brau. The second house, with the hip roof, was the Richard Brush home from 1873 to 1876, now the Imperial Lunch Room. Some of the buildings were later razed or remodeled. The other views, especially 3 and 4, show closeups of the Brush house, seen from the B.M.T. elevated structure.

View 1: About 1900
View 2, 3: 1922
View 4: 1923

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

Jamaica Ave., north side, west from 160th St., showing at the corner the James McLaughlin's Hotel of 1873. Jason Realty Co. composed of Miller, Bernstein and Rappaport sold this place 50x100' for $450,000 according to one Weber a locksmith at 9040 160th St.

May 1923.

160th Street, east side, north of Jamaica, to Ninetieth Avenues, showing to the left of the center, the A. Brinkerhoff house of 1873, at the N.E. corner of the last mentioned point.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

Jamaica, Queens: A general view southeastward across Jamaica, seen from Jamaica Avenue at 160th Street. In the
distance is the Jamaica High School.
P. L. Sperr  April 1, 1932
